  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-01 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across five flow-speed combinations. All thirteen ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are assessed. A primary claim of model adequacy is registered and richly described; ValidationResults carry full provenance chains to experimental evidence. Package decision: Accepted.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-model-adequacy",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-pump-v3",
