      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index comparison — NIH experimental data vs CFD predictions",
      "description": "Predicted hemolysis index (IH) values from CFD were compared against NIH experimental measurements at five operating conditions. Mean absolute percentage error (MAPE) was 18.3%, within the pre-specified ±25% acceptance band. Monte Carlo UQ (N=10,000 Latin hypercube samples) confirmed that 95th-percentile predicted IH remained below the clinical threshold of 0.005 g/100 L at all operating points.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "MAPE < 25%; 95th-percentile IH < 0.005 g/100 L",
      "outcome": "Pass",
