      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence — Grid Convergence Index study",
      "description": "Three systematically refined meshes (coarse 4.2 M, medium 12.6 M, fine 37.8 M cells; refinement ratio r=1.44) were evaluated. GCI for hemolysis index on the fine-to-medium pair was 3.1%, indicating discretization error is within acceptable bounds for MRL 5 requirements.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI < 5% on fine-to-medium mesh pair for hemolysis index QoI",
      "outcome": "Pass",
      "prov:wasDerivedFrom": "https://uofa.net/synth/evidence/mesh-convergence-study-report-rev3",
