      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification — hemolysis prediction uncertainty bounds",
      "description": "Monte Carlo UQ propagated uncertainty in fluid viscosity (±5%), hemolysis model coefficients (±15%), and inlet flow waveform (±8%) through the CFD model using N=10,000 LHS samples. 95% confidence interval on predicted IH spans 0.0021–0.0044 g/100 L at the worst-case operating point, remaining below the clinical threshold.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "95th-percentile IH < 0.005 g/100 L; CI width < 60% of nominal prediction",
